relate-provider

DESCRIPTION
  A provider is a container of DBMSs, it takes care of file system and access to
  the DBMS. Aura and Desktop are providers, and in the case of single DBMS
  instances either locally or remotely, the host is the provider.

USAGE
  relate provider add <name> <path|url>
  relate provider update <name|id>
  relate provider remove <name|id>
  relate provider list [--format=<format>|--ids]
  relate provider use <name|id>
  relate provider current [--format=<format>]

OPTIONS
  --format=<format>       Specify what information should be returned.
  --ids                   Return only IDs.
  --file=<path>           File to load context from.

NOTES
  add:
    If no <path|url> is specified, it should be possible to pass the configuration
    file for the provider through STDIN.
  update:
    Opens the configuration file on the default editor.